I need to identify the tangible items that are held for use in the production or supply of goods or services, for rental to others, or for administrative purposes.

Looking at the balance sheet, these types of assets are typically categorized as fixed assets (also known as property, plant, and equipment or PP&E). Fixed assets represent tangible items used in operations over multiple accounting periods.

From the balance sheet provided, I can see the following line item:
- Fixed Assets: 8,000,000.00 (initial amount on 2023-12-31) and 10,729,032.26 (end amount on 2024-02-05)

This is the line item that represents tangible items held for use in operations.
